quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  35,31,"And what We have revealed to you<sup>sg </sup>of the Scripture is the truth, confirming what preceded it. Allah is most surely All-Aware, All-Seeing of His servants."
  35,32,"Then We gave the Scripture as a heritage to those of Our servants whom We selected: so of them is one who is unjust to himself, and one who follows a middle course, and one who is a forerunner in good deeds—by Allah’s leave. That is what the great grace is."
  35,33,"Gardens of Eden which they enter{1}; they are adorned therein with gold bracelets and pearls{2}, and their garments therein are of silk.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Abu Amr read it as: “…into which they are entered…”],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: All except for Nafie’, Asem and Abu Ja’far read it as: “…with bracelets of gold and (of) pearls…”]
  35,34,"And they said{1}, “All praise be to Allah Who has lifted all sorrow from us; our Lord is most surely Oft-Forgiving, Ever Thankful.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered upon by the reader.
  35,35,"He Who settled us in the Home of Everlasting Stay, by His grace, where neither toil touches us nor fatigue afflicts us.”"
  35,36,"And those who have denied—for them is the fire of Hell wherein they are never finished off and thus die, nor is its punishment lightened for them. Thus We repay every staunch denier{1}.",footnotes:1:Qira’at: Abu Amr read it as: “Thus every staunch denier is repaid.”
  35,37,"And they scream aloud therein, “Our Lord, get us out, that we may act righteously, unlike the way we used to act.” “Did We not give you<sup>pl </sup>a lifelong enough to take warning if you were going to? And the warner did come to you, so taste{1}, for there is no supporter for the unjust.”",footnotes:1:The punishment of your deeds.
  35,38,"Indeed, Allah is the Knower of the hidden realm of the heavens and the earth. Indeed, He is All-Knowing of what lies within the chests."
